        <p><strong>Microsoft Outlook</strong> is a personal information manager from <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>, available as a part of the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Office', 'ITS'); ?> suite.</p>
        <p>Although often used mainly as an email application, it also includes a calendar, task manager, contact manager, note taking, journal, and web browsing.</p>
        <p>It can be used as a stand alone application, or can work with <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Exchange Server', 'IT'); ?> and <strong>Microsoft SharePoint Server</strong> for multiple users in an organization, such as shared mailboxes and calendars, Exchange public folders, SharePoint lists, and meeting schedules.</p>
        <p>There are third-party add-on applications that integrate Outlook with devices such as <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('BlackBerry', 'ITH'); ?> mobile phones and with other software such as Office and Skype internet communication.</p>
